Package org.postgresql.pljava.pgxs

Class ScriptEngineLoader

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.ClassLoader
      • org.postgresql.pljava.pgxs.ScriptEngineLoader
  • class ScriptEngineLoader
extends ClassLoader
    A ClassLoader with (effectively) two parents, the inherited one and Java's platform class loader.

    This loader will be given to the ScriptEngineManager. The inherited loader supplied by Maven does not have Java's platform class loader as its parent (or ancestor), which leaves Java's ServiceLoader mechanism unable to find Nashorn's script engine. Therefore, this loader will declare the Java platform class loader as its actual parent, and search the Maven-supplied class loader for whatever the platform class loader does not find.

    This could pose a risk of class version conflicts if the Maven-supplied loader has defined classes that are also known to the platform loader. It would be safer to delegate to Maven's loader first and the parent as fallback. That would require overriding more of ClassLoader's default functionality, though. With any luck, the targeted use of this loader only with the ScriptEngineManager will minimize the risk, already low because it would be odd to override classes of the Java platform itself.

        protected Enumeration<URL> findResources​(String name)
                                  throws IOException
        Delegate to the Maven-supplied loader for finding a resource.

        This is called by the super implementation of getResources after enumerating the resources available from the parent loader. This method needs only to return the resources available from the Maven-supplied loader; the caller will combine the two enumerations.
